<section id="fs-id2336562" class="free-response">
<title>Critical Thinking Questions</title>
<exercise id="fs-id2033426">
<problem id="fs-id1289140"><para id="fs-id1849563">Describe the processing and presentation of an intracellular antigen.</para></problem>
<solution id="fs-id2068457"><label/>
<para id="fs-id2143706">The antigen is digested by the proteasome, brought into the endoplasmic reticulum by the TAP transporter system, where it binds to class I MHC molecules. These are taken to the cell surface by transport vesicles.</para>
</solution>
</exercise>
<exercise id="fs-id2316133">
<problem id="fs-id2228202"><para id="fs-id1478440">Describe clonal selection and expansion.</para></problem>
<solution id="fs-id2269348"><label/>
<para id="fs-id1708290">Antigen-specific clones are stimulated as their antigen receptor binds to antigen. They are then activated and proliferate, expanding their numbers. The result is a large number of antigen-specific lymphocytes.</para>
</solution>
</exercise>
